By 2016, systems for monitoring disaggregated data and analysis on the situation of children and women are strengthened andregularly updated to inform policy.
By 2016, the capacity of government and civil society is strengthened for the development and implementation of a national policyframework for social protection sensitive to children.
Project Support Costs - management of human capacity
SAO TOME E PRINCIPE COUNTRY PROGRAMME 20
By 2016, policy documents that strengthen the National Health System (SNS) include the rights of children and women.
By 2016, capacity of district health centres to provide and monitor basic health care, including HIV/AIDS care, is strengthened.

By 2016 vulnerable communities and families will have strengthed capacity and knowledge to adopt essential family practices (ORT,hand washing with soap, sleeping under impregnated mosquito nets, PMTCT) to improve child survival and the protection of childrenand women.

By 2016, children from 0-6yrs, particularly in the most vulnerable areas, benefit from improved access to, and quality of earlychildhood development through the reducation of barriers to early childhood education.
By 2016, school principals, teachers and parents have strengthened capacity to promote a quality education as a part of the ChildFriendly School initiative.
By 2016, national legislation and regulations for the protection of children and women are strengthened and fully in-line withinternational conventions ratified by Sao Tome and Principe.
Increased capacity on child protection  ociety organisations will have enhanced capacity to ensure better monitoring of childrenand women who are victims of violence, abuse and exploitation.
